Home
›
About Fenway
All That Jazz
Built in 1924, Fenway Hotel is an icon of the jazz age. Throughout its time as an operating hotel, the Grand Lady of Dunedin has hosted explorers, artists, politicians, musicians and more. With walls echoing its musical heritage, the hotel earned a place in history by serving as the county’s first radio station. It’s by bringing these elements together that we create the new vision for Fenway Hotel and a destination unlike any other.
Fenway Timeline
County’s First Radio Station
In addition to serving as a destination for vacationers, Fenway Hotel served as the county’s first radio station from 1925-1927.
Top Beaches
Located on St. Joseph Sound, the property faces Caladesi and Honeymoon Islands, named top beaches in the world.
The Fenway is a place humming with soul
Where songs of the last century vibrate in the walls and every footstep through the halls. Here, guests and locals come together to dance the night away. Like the jazz bands that played on the airwaves here years before, everyone takes their turn to add a layer to the experience that is Fenway Hotel. Each day, they channel the energy of the past while looking to each other to keep the good times rolling.
At Fenway Hotel, we amplify the carefree Floridian spirit of ‘figuring it out as you go’ and invite others to join in. No two listens are ever the quite the same so tune in, turn up the volume, and don’t touch that dial. Discover for yourself what’s kept us moving all along - the rhythm of Fenway Hotel.
What We Do
The ability to improvise and play along have driven Fenway Hotel since the day it opened its doors. Today, we channel spontaneity and creativity so that no two visits are ever the same.
How We Do It
With touches of the past in a modern setting, a spirit of finding the tune as you go, and an emphasis on the importance of music, we celebrate and channel the history of Fenway Hotel through its roots in live radio.
The Rhythm of Fenway Hotel is Timeless
h2
Tune into the Community
Those who stay at Fenway Hotel are looking for experiences unlike any other, and they’ll find them here in Dunedin. We not only help guests experience the culture beyond the hotel, but find ways in our day-to-day to make Fenway Hotel a gathering place for the community.
Channel The Rhythm
The unique history of Fenway Hotel and the community of Dunedin play important roles in a guest’s stay. We draw inspiration from the things we’ve learned to create an experience immersed in history while leaving room to grow in the future.
Play In The Moment
In jazz, each musician brings their own personality and riffs off of those they perform with. Each player is present and able to adapt on a moment’s notice. Fenway Hotel thrives when we’re searching for the next classic. We listen to each other and our guests to find new ways to add to our evolving tune.

About Hi-Fi
A sun-kissed breathtaking escape. Originally home to WGHB in 1925. Hi-Fi speaks to both high-fidelity sound reproduction, especially as it relates to radio, and the quality of the experience to be had at the bar. Drink in the views of Caladesi and Honeymoon Islands as you savor creatively constructed cocktails, local craft beers and carefully selected wines.
